1602216000.title: Bargain Hunt
1602216000.descr: The Cornwall Royal Showground is the venue for today's Bargain Hunt. Presenter Anita Manning is in the driving seat as two teams of best friends compete to make the most profit at auction. They're all very competitive but who will take home a coveted Gold Gavel?

1602218700.title: Last of the Summer Wine
1602218700.descr: Clegg is writing his memoirs, but is having trouble remembering people's names; Clegg, Truly and Billy meet a man who wants to sail to Ilkley in an inflatable swan, unfortunately it has developed a puncture which Entwistle repairs; Clegg climbs a tree so he can see the church clock, unfortunately he gets stuck; Tom and Entwistle try to cheer Smiler up after he has been dumped by Hermione.

1602220500.title: Call the Midwife
1602220500.descr: Period drama series set in East London in the 1950s, following the life and work of a young midwife Jenny Lee and her colleagues at the Nonnatus House nursing convent. They serve the poor society of Poplar, London. Their main duty is to help bring safe birth to women and help them look after their newborns.

1602223800.title: DIY SOS: The Big Build
1602223800.descr: Take a family in desperate need of help in their home. Add some local tradesmen, lot's of generosity and a bucket load of community spirit. You've got yourself the recipe for DIY SOS. Nick Knowles, along with him team of home improvement experts, and lot's of happy volunteers from the communities of Britain pitch in to make life changing modifications to the homes of families who need them most.

1602231300.title: Bargain Hunt
1602231300.descr: Two teams of amateur antique collectors meet at an antiques fair to compete to make the largest profit from a three hundred pound budget. Once the contestants have done the shopping for their own items, the experts then take any leftover money and go shopping for more antiques which is 'bonus buys'. The teams then have to decide whether or not to take these items to auction.

1602234000.title: Father Brown
1602234000.descr: Father Brown is invited to a party organized by Uncle Mirth, a former music hall comedian. Years ago the priest helped committing him to an asylum, and now he's released and wants revenge. The party is in a warehouse, and death certificates are awaiting the quests.

1602267300.title: Doctor Who
1602267300.descr: Peter Capaldi, Pearl Mackie, Matt Lucas, Kieran Bew, Justin Salinger, Peter Caulfield. "Space – the final frontier. Final because it wants to kill us." Trapped on a space station with no oxygen, the Doctor, Bill and Nardole are horrified to discover the automated spacesuits keeping them alive are also trying to kill them!

1602270000.title: Wodehouse in Exile
1602270000.descr: An intimate film featuring an all-star cast about how the author PG Wodehouse came to face a charge of treason during the Second World War and how this quintessential Englishman, creator of Jeeves and Wooster, became an exile from his own country and never set foot on English soil again.

1602275100.title: Josh
1602275100.descr: Josh Widdlecombe's (comedian) fun loving comedy on living in North London, and the laughs you can have when living with your two best friends. Kate, Owen and Josh share awkward and laughable adult moments in the sitcom, some including their weird landlord, Geoff.

1602276900.title: W1A
1602276900.descr: Following on from the BAFTA award-winning Twenty Twelve: the BBC has a new Head of Values, Ian Fletcher and he's been given the huge task of sorting the corporation out, he has to "restructure" it. The BBC is becoming under a huge load of pressure with the content that they produce. This British comedy is the BBC realising where it goes wrong and is essentially criticising itself.
